Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into small pieces (they should fit neatly on the flatbreads).

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{4.5%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until bright green and slightly crispy, ~{12-15%minutes}. Transfer roasted broccoli to a small #bowl{}.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

While sausage cooks, in a second small bowl, mix @ricotta cheese{4%ounce} with @olive oil{1/2%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Once broccoli is done, place @flatbreads{2} on same #sheet{}. Evenly spread flatbreads with ricotta, then top with broccoli and sausage. Bake on top rack until edges are golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Transfer flatbreads to a #cutting board{} and slice into pieces. Drizzle with @honey{2%teaspoon} and sprinkle with @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Divide between plates and serve.

> For crispier flatbreads, bake 2-4 minutes more.